<bibRefCitation id="AD701EF504D6FF55FA86FF5476C210E0" author="Mortensen" firstAuthor="Mortensen" pageId="134" pageNumber="135" pagination="1 - 200" refId="ref192287" refString="Mortensen, T. (1907) Echinoidea (Part 2). In: The Danish Ingolf-Expedition 1895 - 1896. 4 (2). Bianco Luno, Copenhagen, pp. 1 - 200." type="book chapter" year="1907">Mortensen 1907</bibRefCitation>
) and the Josephine, Tropic and Meteor seamounts (
<bibRefCitation id="AD701EF504D6FF55FCB0FF7175AE10E0" author="Mironov" box="[788,956,188,215]" firstAuthor="Mironov" pageId="134" pageNumber="135" pagination="96 - 133" refId="ref191675" refString="Mironov, A. N. (2006) Echinoids from seamounts of the north-eastern Atlantic, onshore / offshore gradients in species distribution. In: Mironov, A. N., Gebruk, A. V. &amp; Southward, A. J. (Eds.), Biogeography of the North Atlantic Seamounts. KMK Scientific Press, Russian Academy of Sciences, P. P. Shirshov Institute of Oceanology, Moscow, pp. 96 - 133." type="book chapter" year="2006">Mironov 2006</bibRefCitation>
). The subspecies 
<taxonomicName id="0EE1188704D6FF55FB24FF70771510CC" authority="scaber de Meijere, 1903" authorityName="de Meijere" authorityYear="1903" class="Echinoidea" family="Echinocyamidae" genus="Echinocyamus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Clypeasteroida" pageId="134" pageNumber="135" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="subSpecies" species="scaber" subSpecies="scaber">
<emphasis id="FB95BF1604D6FF55FB24FF70732F10E1" box="[1152,1341,188,214]" italics="true" pageId="134" pageNumber="135">E. scaber scaber</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="AD701EF504D6FF55FAE0FF71771510CC" author="Meijere, J. C. H. de" firstAuthor="de Meijere" pageId="134" pageNumber="135" pagination="1 - 16" refId="ref190326" refString="Meijere, J. C. H. de (1903) Vorlaufige Beschreibung der neuen, durch die Siboga-Expedition gesammelten Echiniden. Tijdschrift der Nederlandsche Dierkundige Vereeniging, Series 2, 8 (1), 1 - 16." type="journal article" year="1903">de Meijere, 1903</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
is reported from the Indo-Pacific (
<bibRefCitation id="AD701EF504D6FF55FD28FF2D75F710CC" author="Mironov &amp; Sagaidachny" box="[652,997,224,251]" firstAuthor="Mironov" pageId="134" pageNumber="135" pagination="179 - 204" refId="ref191932" refString="Mironov, A. N. &amp; Sagaidachny, A. Y. (1984) [Morphology and distribution of the recent echinoids of the genus Echinocyamus (Echinoidea: Fibulariidae)]. Trudy Instituta Okeanologii AN, USSR, 119, 179 - 204. [in Russian, English summary]" type="journal article" year="1984">Mironov &amp; Sagaidachny 1984</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
