<paragraph id="C95E630404D6FF55FF63FEBC77CF1255" blockId="134.[151,1437,152,611]" pageId="134" pageNumber="135">
<emphasis id="FB95BF1604D6FF55FF63FEBC772F11BC" bold="true" box="[199,317,369,395]" pageId="134" pageNumber="135">Remarks:</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="AD701EF504D6FF55FEE0FEBC741C11BC" author="Mortensen" box="[324,526,369,395]" firstAuthor="Mortensen" pageId="134" pageNumber="135" pagination="1 - 200" refId="ref192287" refString="Mortensen, T. (1907) Echinoidea (Part 2). In: The Danish Ingolf-Expedition 1895 - 1896. 4 (2). Bianco Luno, Copenhagen, pp. 1 - 200." type="book chapter" year="1907">Mortensen (1907)</bibRefCitation>
described two species of 
<taxonomicName id="0EE1188704D6FF55FC8AFEBD75C311BD" authorityName=", Mortensen" authorityYear="1907" box="[814,977,368,394]" class="Echinoidea" family="Echinocyamidae" genus="Echinocyamus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Clypeasteroida" pageId="134" pageNumber="135" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="FB95BF1604D6FF55FC8AFEBD75C311BD" box="[814,977,368,394]" italics="true" pageId="134" pageNumber="135">Echinocyamus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="0EE1188704D6FF55FC44FEBC728111BD" authorityName="$ Mortensen" authorityYear="1907" box="[992,1171,369,394]" class="Echinoidea" family="Echinocyamidae" genus="Echinocyamus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Clypeasteroida" pageId="134" pageNumber="135" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="species" species="macrostomus">
<emphasis id="FB95BF1604D6FF55FC44FEBC728111BD" box="[992,1171,369,394]" italics="true" pageId="134" pageNumber="135">E. macrostomus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="0EE1188704D6FF55FB6DFEBC736111BD" authorityName="$ Mortensen" authorityYear="1907" box="[1225,1395,368,394]" class="Echinoidea" family="Echinocyamidae" genus="Echinocyamus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Clypeasteroida" pageId="134" pageNumber="135" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="species" species="grandiporus">
<emphasis id="FB95BF1604D6FF55FB6DFEBC736111BD" box="[1225,1395,368,394]" italics="true" pageId="134" pageNumber="135">E. grandiporus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
using material, which included animals collected in Azorean deep waters. 
<bibRefCitation id="AD701EF504D6FF55FC66FE58729E1198" author="Mortensen" box="[962,1164,405,431]" firstAuthor="Mortensen" pageId="134" pageNumber="135" pagination="1 - 200" refId="ref192287" refString="Mortensen, T. (1907) Echinoidea (Part 2). In: The Danish Ingolf-Expedition 1895 - 1896. 4 (2). Bianco Luno, Copenhagen, pp. 1 - 200." type="book chapter" year="1907">Mortensen (1907)</bibRefCitation>
considered his two new deep-water species closely related though 
<taxonomicName id="0EE1188704D6FF55FDD7FE74753511E5" authorityName="$ Mortensen" authorityYear="1907" box="[627,807,441,466]" class="Echinoidea" family="Echinocyamidae" genus="Echinocyamus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Clypeasteroida" pageId="134" pageNumber="135" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="species" species="macrostomus">
<emphasis id="FB95BF1604D6FF55FDD7FE74753511E5" box="[627,807,441,466]" italics="true" pageId="134" pageNumber="135">E. macrostomus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
tended to live in deeper waters. In contrast, 
<bibRefCitation id="AD701EF504D6FF55FAB9FE75776A11C0" author="Mironov &amp; Sagaidachny" firstAuthor="Mironov" pageId="134" pageNumber="135" pagination="179 - 204" refId="ref191932" refString="Mironov, A. N. &amp; Sagaidachny, A. Y. (1984) [Morphology and distribution of the recent echinoids of the genus Echinocyamus (Echinoidea: Fibulariidae)]. Trudy Instituta Okeanologii AN, USSR, 119, 179 - 204. [in Russian, English summary]" type="journal article" year="1984">Mironov &amp; Sagaidachny (1984)</bibRefCitation>
considered 
<taxonomicName id="0EE1188704D6FF55FE5BFE1074A011C1" authorityName="$ Mortensen" authorityYear="1907" box="[511,690,477,502]" class="Echinoidea" family="Echinocyamidae" genus="Echinocyamus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Clypeasteroida" pageId="134" pageNumber="135" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="species" species="macrostomus">
<emphasis id="FB95BF1604D6FF55FE5BFE1074A011C1" box="[511,690,477,502]" italics="true" pageId="134" pageNumber="135">E. macrostomus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
closely related with 
<taxonomicName id="0EE1188704D6FF55FC3FFE10721711C1" authorityName="de Meijere" authorityYear="1903" box="[923,1029,476,502]" class="Echinoidea" family="Echinocyamidae" genus="Echinocyamus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Clypeasteroida" pageId="134" pageNumber="135" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="species" species="scaber">
<emphasis id="FB95BF1604D6FF55FC3FFE10721711C1" box="[923,1029,476,502]" italics="true" pageId="134" pageNumber="135">E. scaber</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and downgraded Mortensen species to a variety of the later. Additionally, 
<bibRefCitation id="AD701EF504D6FF55FD99FDCD74E3122C" author="Mironov" box="[573,753,512,539]" firstAuthor="Mironov" pageId="134" pageNumber="135" pagination="96 - 133" refId="ref191675" refString="Mironov, A. N. (2006) Echinoids from seamounts of the north-eastern Atlantic, onshore / offshore gradients in species distribution. In: Mironov, A. N., Gebruk, A. V. &amp; Southward, A. J. (Eds.), Biogeography of the North Atlantic Seamounts. KMK Scientific Press, Russian Academy of Sciences, P. P. Shirshov Institute of Oceanology, Moscow, pp. 96 - 133." type="book chapter" year="2006">Mironov (2006)</bibRefCitation>
observed that some of the specimens from Meteor and Antialtair seamounts presented intermediate characteristics between this subspecies and 
<taxonomicName id="0EE1188704D6FF55FB9AFDE872F41209" authorityName="$ Mortensen" authorityYear="1907" box="[1086,1254,548,574]" class="Echinoidea" family="Echinocyamidae" genus="Echinocyamus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Clypeasteroida" pageId="134" pageNumber="135" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="species" species="grandiporus">
<emphasis id="FB95BF1604D6FF55FB9AFDE872F41209" box="[1086,1254,548,574]" italics="true" pageId="134" pageNumber="135">E. grandiporus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, suggesting that they could represent hybrids.
</paragraph>
